    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bookbinding morocco, often levant, that has had its grain flattened before it has been attached to the book boards, then, after it is on the boards, polished very smooth.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
